	<tr>
	<td colspan="4" class="mid">
      
      <p>Very remarkable! Admirable! The Wolfram Language can have a profound impact in research and education in Mathematics. Projects like Theorema 2.0 can leverage the Wolfram Language creations to foster a new paradigm of research and collaboration, in which smart formats like CDFs can substitute old journal formats, for instance, and mathematical content can be accessible efficiently through the Internet!<br />
Deeply interested in how an increasing network of mathematicians, scientists and engineers can leverage these new powers to create a global (computational!) knowledge bases of definitions, proved theorems, models and algorithms, in a way that scales the outcome of the efforts of professionals, and uses the Internet and machine learning capabilities to engineer coordinated discovery and create meaningful professional connections.<br />
Deeply interested also in how these portable computational knowledge can have a profound impact in creating educational content, or program chips, etc!</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
